column5: Got out early at Innisfill Beach for closing day for whities. Ramp to lake was quite torn up. Lots of people out for the day. After heading out to 80+ feet of water & setting up things started happening. I quickly had a fish on shortly followed by another. Not long after things slowed down for our group of three. 3 total whities for the 3 of us. Marking lots of fish which would come up & look at our baits but would not hit. Moved 3 times and tried many types of baits with same results. Finally moved in for a few perch to close off the day. Here's the two I caught to start the day.  Largest was 27" and 6 1/4 lbs.  Best Wishes: Rick
nice going  done for another year
Thanks guys. It sure seemed to be a good year off Innisfil Beach. Terry these fish were caught not far from where I remember watching you catching that 31" laker a few years ago.  Tight Lines: Rick
that's where I got my whitefish on Saturday, been a good area this year
That's not you. That guy's not wearing a GB hat.  JF
What a great way to end the season.... congratulations Woodsman  Those are real nice looking Thanks for sharing Leechman
John: The grey hood you can see around my neck is attached to my Green Bay Packers sweatshirt.  Rick
Great closing for sure Rick. Congrats to you. It's on to the softwater now....
Great stuff woodsman.....really nice whitie that big one....they can be buggers, marking lots and no takers....gggrrrrrrr!
